EU Carbon Permits Fall by 1.1% on Lower German Power and Crude Oil Prices

-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 
2011-05-06T07:25:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/eu-carbon-permits-fall-by-1-1-on-lower-german-power-and-crude-oil-prices.html
European Union carbon permits dropped
to their lowest since April 26 as German power and crude oil
declined on concern slow economic growth will curb demand.  EU allowances for December fell as much as 1.1 percent to
16.79 euros ($24.43) a metric ton on  London â€™s ICE Futures Europe
exchange as of 8:20 a.m.   Brent crude  dropped as much as 1 percent in London after
tumbling 8.6 percent yesterday. It was at $110.45 a barrel as of
8:23 a.m. German power for 2012 decreased as much as 0.9 percent
to 57.85 euros a megawatt-hour before rising to 58.05 euros,
according to prices from brokers compiled by
